                            <comment id="38306" author="pjones" created="Tue, 8 May 2012 11:05:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1365&quot; title=&quot;Implement ldiskfs LARGEDIR support for e2fsprogs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1365&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1365&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="38305" author="liang" created="Tue, 8 May 2012 11:02:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;for 1.8.7 and 2.1.x, the limit is still same with ext3/ext4.&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs of 2.2 can support larger directory (4-level htree which can support over a billion files under directory), but we need make some changes to e2fsprogs before you can use it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t have plan to backport the ldiskfs patch from 2.2 to 1.8.x yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;here is the tracking ticket: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1365&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1365&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess we can just close this one and use &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1365&quot; title=&quot;Implement ldiskfs LARGEDIR support for e2fsprogs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1365&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1365&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
